  "content": "e`/`node.source_origin`. These fields must appear in the server JSON responses.\n\n**Update `entry_detail_handler`** (dashboard/mod.rs ~line 642) — add new fields to the metadata object:\n\n```rust\n\"metadata\": {\n    \"source_file\": entry.metadata.source_file,\n    \"language\": entry.metadata.language,\n    \"content_role\": entry.metadata.content_role,\n    \"source_origin\": entry.metadata.source_origin,\n},\n```\n\n**Update `graph_scope_handler`** — add new fields to each node's JSON in the nodes array:\n\n```rust\n\"content_role\": node.metadata.content_role,\n\"source_origin\": node.metadata.source_origin,\n```\n\nAlso update the `entry_history_handler` similarly so history entries carry the metadata.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Build and verify**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo build -p corvia-server`\nExpected: Compiles\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-server/src/dashboard/mod.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(dashboard): add content_role/source_origin to all dashboard JSON responses\"\n```\n\n---\n",
